01/06/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- NATO has requested that Bulgaria send more troops to Afghanistan as part of the International Security Assistance Force.
The chief of the Bulgarian Army's general staff, General Nikola Kolev, said Monday (31 May) that 200 more Bulgarian soldiers would be sent to Afghanistan over the next six months.
Currently, 66 Bulgarian soldiers are there.
(Sega - 01/06/04)
